# Wavefront OBJ file for a square-based pyramid
# Created by Gemini on September 20, 2025
#
# This model contains vertex, texture coordinate, and normal data.
# The geometry is a 2x2 unit base on the XZ plane, centered at the origin,
# with an apex 1 unit high on the Y-axis.
# This version uses only triangles.

# -- Vertices (v) --
# Total: 5 vertices
# Format: v x y z
v -1.0 -1.0 1.0   # Vertex 1: base, front-left
v 1.0 -1.0 1.0    # Vertex 2: base, front-right
v 1.0 -1.0 -1.0   # Vertex 3: base, back-right
v -1.0 -1.0 -1.0  # Vertex 4: base, back-left
v 0.0 1.0 0.0     # Vertex 5: apex (top point)

# -- Texture Coordinates (vt) --
# Total: 8 coordinates
# This layout corresponds to a cross-shaped "unwrapped" texture map.
# Format: vt u v
vt 0.25 0.25  # UV 1: for base, front-left
vt 0.75 0.25  # UV 2: for base, front-right
vt 0.75 0.75  # UV 3: for base, back-right
vt 0.25 0.75  # UV 4: for base, back-left
vt 0.5 1.0    # UV 5: apex, for front face
vt 1.0 0.5    # UV 6: apex, for right face
vt 0.5 0.0    # UV 7: apex, for back face
vt 0.0 0.5    # UV 8: apex, for left face

# -- Normals (vn) --
# Total: 5 normals (one for each face), pre-normalized.
# Format: vn x y z
vn 0.0 -1.0 0.0      # Normal 1: base face (pointing down)
vn 0.0 0.4472 0.8944  # Normal 2: front face
vn 0.8944 0.4472 0.0  # Normal 3: right face
vn 0.0 0.4472 -0.8944 # Normal 4: back face
vn -0.8944 0.4472 0.0 # Normal 5: left face

# -- Faces (f) --
# Total: 6 faces (all triangles)
# Format: f v1/vt1/vn1 v2/vt2/vn2 v3/vt3/vn3

# Base faces (split from one quad into two triangles)
# Both triangles share the same downward-facing normal (vn1).
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1
f 1/1/1 3/3/1 4/4/1

# The four triangular side faces
# Each face points to its own normal for flat shading.
f 1/1/2 5/5/2 2/2/2   # Front face
f 2/2/3 5/6/3 3/3/3   # Right face
f 3/3/4 5/7/4 4/4/4   # Back face
f 4/4/5 5/8/5 1/1/5   # Left face

# End of file